            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://www.gamespot.com/articles/the-outlast-trials-new-season-includes-a-ton-of-free-and-unsettling-cosmetics/1100-6530360/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><p>
    <span data-nosnippet="">GameSpot may receive revenue from affiliate and advertising partnerships for sharing this content and from purchases through links.</span>
  </p><article itemscope="" data-type-id="1100" data-guid="1100-6530360">

            
            
  


        

  


        
        
              <section>

                  
          <div data-content-element-selector="p, .js-buylink-item-container" data-allowed-classes-selector="js-buylink-item-container">
                <p><a href="https://www.gamespot.com/games/the-outlast-trials/" data-ref-id="5000-505577">The Outlast Trials</a> update 2.1 has arrived, bringing new limited-time events, missions, and a whole bunch of new cosmetics, including several skins in a game already chock full of some of the creepiest character costumes in all of video games. The free update is out now on PC, Xbox Series X|S, and PS5.</p><p>Two new MK-Challenges, the game's shorter-form missions, debut as Stash the Contraband and Kidnap the Mistress. Like other missions in the game, these are contextualized as brainwashing exercises, as the seedy Murkoff corporation attempts to get you to bend to their will before they release you as a sleeper agent sent into the world to cause Cold War-era chaos.</p><p>A bonus page of high-end cosmetics has been added to last season's Catalog, the game's free battle pass system, while a whole new Catalog is out now, too. It includes several skins, including one that resembles the Zodiac Killer's famous get-up. It's just the latest creepy skin in this game which seems to pride itself on its depraved cosmetics.</p><figure data-align="center" data-size="large" data-img-src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1632/16320660/4465083-screenshot2025-03-25113613.png" data-ref-id="1300-4465083" data-ratio="0.56455696202532" data-width="790" data-embed-type="image"><a href="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1632/16320660/4465083-screenshot2025-03-25113613.png" data-ref-id="1300-4465083"></a><figcaption>The new Outlast Trials Catalog (battle pass) is framed around the vigilante Amelia character currently trying to topple the villains of the story.</figcaption><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1632/16320660/4465083-screenshot2025-03-25113613.png"></figure><figure data-embed-type="gallery" data-img-src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1632/16320660/4465084-tot_steam_800x450_1.png,https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1632/16320660/4465085-screens2.png,https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1632/16320660/4465086-screens1.png,https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1632/16320660/4465087-catalog2.png" data-ref-id="1300-4465084,1300-4465085,1300-4465086,1300-4465087" data-resize-urls="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/square_avatar/1632/16320660/4465084-tot_steam_800x450_1.png,https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/square_avatar/1632/16320660/4465085-screens2.png,https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/square_avatar/1632/16320660/4465086-screens1.png,https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/square_avatar/1632/16320660/4465087-catalog2.png"><p>Gallery</p>     <img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1632/16320660/4465084-tot_steam_800x450_1.png,https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1632/16320660/4465085-screens2.png,https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1632/16320660/4465086-screens1.png,https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1632/16320660/4465087-catalog2.png"></figure><p>The Outlast Trials is also celebrating its first anniversary, so there are even more free cosmetics, such as a nausea-inducing cake, to be unlocked by completing the first-anniversary challenges. Both the new Catalog and these anniversary cosmetics are limited-time offerings, with them disappearing from the game in about a month on April 22.</p><p>As for game fixes, several Rigs (equippable cooldown abilities) have been buffed. The Barricade Rig can now apply to more doors and windows, locking them and slowing enemy pursuit. The Bling Rig now deploys faster at three seconds for its upgraded version or four seconds for its base version--each figure comes down one second from before the patch. The newest Rig, the Jammer, can now open mannequin gates the likes of which can be found in the nursery map.</p><p>The easiest difficulty also got a little easier, too, as enemies inflict less damage and move slightly slower. However, if all this sounds quite generous, it's not without some other punishing changes; the hardest difficulty, Psychosurgery, now features "slightly faster" enemies, as well. The full patch notes are found below:</p><h2>The Outlast Trials 2.1 update: Bug fixes and updates</h2><ul><li>Barricade Rig: Can now be deployed in more doorways and window frames.</li><li>Blind Rig: Base deploy decreased to 4 seconds (was 5 seconds), the upgraded is now 3s (was 4s).</li><li>Jammer: Jammer can now open automatic mannequin gates.</li><li>The nearest Revive Syringe location is now displayed to teammates when someone from the team dies.</li><li>Replay Introduction now displays a confirmation popup before launching.</li><li>The “Introductory” Difficulty has been adjusted for enemies to inflict less damages and move slightly slower.</li><li>The “Psychosurgery” Difficulty has been adjusted to slightly increase enemy speed.</li><li>The “Stay Together” Variator has been removed from Escalation Therapy.</li><li>Using the “Regroup” quick chat action now places a regroup icon on the ground at the player’s location.</li><li>Programs: A new visual indication is displayed for Trials completed in other difficulties than the one that is currently selected on the Trial Board.</li><li>Posters: Posters are now ordered by type (Weekly Programs, Events, etc.)</li><li>Settings: Added a new option to toggle mouse smoothing.</li></ul>
  
                        
    
        
        
  
                                  </div>

          
        
                              
            <span>
        <a itemprop="reviewer" href="https://plus.google.com/111003174123010839883?rel=author">Mark Delaney</a> on Google+
      </span>
      
                    
  
    
          
            
